The paper deals with computer vision problems and proposes a new method for linking between different domains without prior correspondences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new unsupervised method for correlation analysis, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions text and images, suggesting that it could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents results on CCA benchmarks, which could indicate that it is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
